ers implicated a number of genes, several previously associated with nicotine exposure.$\backslash$n$\backslash$nCONCLUSIONS: RNA sequencing identifies distinct and consistent differences in gene expression between brain regions, with non-coding RNA displaying greater diversity between brain regions than mRNAs. Numerous RNAs exhibit robust allele selective expression, proving a means for discovery of cis-acting regulatory factors with potential clinical relevance.},
